summary: I CAN'T PINPOINT THE MONTH OR TIME IT HAPPENED, BUT A COUPLE OF YEARS AGO I STARTED TO NOTICE THAT THE GAS MILEAGE IN MY 1996 PLYMOUTH GRAND VOYAGER HAD DROPPED CONSIDERABLY.  IT ONLY GETS ABOUT 15 MPG AROUND TOWN AND ONLY 18 TO 19 MPG IN HIGHWAY DRIVING.  I'VE TAKEN IT TO THE DEALERSHIP AND THEY PERFORMED THEIR 'DIAGNOSTICS' AND TOLD ME NOTHING IS WRONG AND SENT ME BACK HOME WITH THE MINI-VAN STILL GETTING LOUSY GAS MILEAGE.
